Implemented the ambiguity-policy update for `modal.compiler.ambiguity` by adding explicit dynamic-family outvote detection.

**Changes**
- Added a dynamic-family outvote margin config and wired it into family ambiguity evaluation in [compiler.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-hour-20260518T031511Z-codex/worktrees/agent-codex-program-synthesis-uscode-modal-hour-20260518T031511Z-codex-packet-000006-20260518_033558/ipfs_datasets_py/logic/modal/compiler.py:55) and [compiler.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-hour-20260518T031511Z-codex/worktrees/agent-codex-program-synthesis-uscode-modal-hour-20260518T031511Z-codex-packet-000006-20260518_033558/ipfs_datasets_py/logic/modal/compiler.py:372).
- Added new ambiguity rule `dynamic_scope_family_outvoted` with deterministic metadata (`predicted_family`, `target_family`, `family_margin`, lexical signals) in [compiler.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-hour-20260518T031511Z-codex/worktrees/agent-codex-program-synthesis-uscode-modal-hour-20260518T031511Z-codex-packet-000006-20260518_033558/ipfs_datasets_py/logic/modal/compiler.py:791).
- Added deterministic dynamic lexical/scope signals (`has_dynamic_cue`, `has_dynamic_scope`, `has_dynamic_scope_phrase`) in [spacy_modal_codec.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-hour-20260518T031511Z-codex/worktrees/agent-codex-program-synthesis-uscode-modal-hour-20260518T031511Z-codex-packet-000006-20260518_033558/ipfs_datasets_py/optimizers/logic_theorem_optimizer/spacy_modal_codec.py:117) and [spacy_modal_codec.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-hour-20260518T031511Z-codex/worktrees/agent-codex-program-synthesis-uscode-modal-hour-20260518T031511Z-codex-packet-000006-20260518_033558/ipfs_datasets_py/optimizers/logic_theorem_optimizer/spacy_modal_codec.py:623).
- Added targeted unit tests for dynamic ambiguity, including an inflected no-cue case (`filed`) in [test_modal_codec.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-hour-20260518T031511Z-codex/worktrees/agent-codex-program-synthesis-uscode-modal-hour-20260518T031511Z-codex-packet-000006-20260518_033558/tests/unit_tests/logic/modal/test_modal_codec.py:620) and [test_modal_codec.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-hour-20260518T031511Z-codex/worktrees/agent-codex-program-synthesis-uscode-modal-hour-20260518T031511Z-codex-packet-000006-20260518_033558/tests/unit_tests/logic/modal/test_modal_codec.py:646).

